Author: Sunopsis Version: 4.0 Last Update: DEC-2004
Description: - Loading Knowledge Module - Loads data from any ISO-92 to a DB2/400 using OS command CPYFRMIPF - This module uses Sunopsis Command SnpsSqlUnload to extract data in a temporary file. Data is loaded into the target temporary DB2/400 table which is created dynamically using the CPYFRMIPF OS command.
Restrictions: - The option DEFAULT_DIRECTORY indicates the location of the temporary generated file. - A ODI Agent must be located on the AS/400.
Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (tables, files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.
Temp. Directory for the data file
Directory where the temporary data file is created by ODI. This directory must be a valid path on the AS400 Examples: /temp

CALL QSYS.QCMDEXC('CPYFRMIMPF FROMSTMF("<%=snpRef.getUserExit("DEFAULT_DIRECTORY")%>/<%=snpRef.getInfo("TARG_NAME")%>.exp") TOFILE(<%=snpRef.getTargetTable("WORK_SCHEMA")%>/<%=snpRef.getInfo("COLL_NAME")%>) MBROPT(*REPLACE) RCDDLM(*CRLF) STRDLM(*NONE) FLDDLM(*TAB) ' , 0000000130.00000)

<% if ("C".equals(snpRef.getJrnInfo( "JRN_METHOD"))) { %> /* Consistant journalization detected. */ /* Lock should be done by a specific step in a package */ <% } else { %> delete from <%=snpRef.getTable("L","JRN_NAME","A")%> where JRN_CONSUMED = '1' <%=snpRef.getJrnFilter()%> <% } %>

<% if ("C".equals(snpRef.getJrnInfo( "JRN_METHOD"))) { %> /* Consistant journalization detected. */ /* Lock should be done by a specific step in a package */ <% } else { %> update <%=snpRef.getTable( "L" , "JRN_NAME" , "A" )%> set JRN_CONSUMED = '1' where (1=1) <%=snpRef.getJrnFilter()%> <% } %>
